Location Data Collection
The U-Haul Vehicle, Towable Equipment (including U-Haul Trailer, U-Box Trailer, Auto Transport, Tow Dolly, Motorcycle Trailer), and/or U-Box Container(s) in your possession (collectively, "U-Haul Equipment") may be equipped with a device which collects location data of the U-Haul Equipment ("Location Detection Device"). We may access and/or use the Location Detection Device in the event of the following:

U-Haul Equipment is not returned at the time and location stated on the U-Haul Equipment Contract or any addendums thereto;
Upon notice of illegal activity or other violation of the terms and conditions found in the U-Haul Equipment Contract or U-Box Contract;
If the U-Haul Equipment is reported missing, stolen, or abandoned to law enforcement or an entity within the U-Haul System;
For the purposes of roadside assistance or other related services to the U-Haul Equipment;
If requested by law enforcement or other appropriate governmental agency or court order and/or to comply with any legal or regulatory requirements;
In the event of an emergency and/or to assist in dispatching emergency services;
To monitor U-Haul Equipment for diagnostic, performance, repair, maintenance, and design purposes;
To monitor U-Haul Equipment for fleet performance, migration, positioning, and repositioning purposes;
To provide you with important information related to U-Haul locations, return details, or other information that will provide you with better services; and/or
For any other legitimate business purposes as authorized by law.

